    'am.vs.0.t': 'Asset management vs investment banking',
    'am.vs.0.d': 'Asset management invests money for clients over time. Banking arranges one-off transactions and deals for a fee.',
    'am.vs.1.t': 'Asset management vs private equity',
    'am.vs.1.d': 'Asset management mostly invests in listed securities. Private equity buys and owns whole companies.',
    'am.vs.2.t': 'Asset management vs hedge funds',
    'am.vs.2.d': 'Traditional asset management is often long-only and benchmark-driven. Hedge funds use broader strategies and can short.',
    'am.vs.3.t': 'Asset management vs wealth management',
    'am.vs.3.d': 'Wealth management builds a personalised financial plan and portfolio for one client relationship at a time, often across products from several providers. Asset management runs pooled funds or institutional mandates according to one strategy applied across many investors.',
    'am.vs.4.t': 'Asset management vs sales and trading',
    'am.vs.4.d': 'Trading desks buy and sell securities to provide liquidity, execute client orders or take short-term market views, often holding positions for hours or days. Asset management makes longer-horizon investment decisions and typically relies on trading desks to execute the resulting trades.',
    'am.vs.5.t': 'Asset management vs equity research',
    'am.vs.5.d': 'Sell-side equity research publishes research and recommendations for a bank or broker’s external clients. Asset management uses its own, internal research to actually invest and manage the portfolio.',
