    'ma.faq.0.q': 'What is M&A advisory?',
    'ma.faq.0.a': 'M&A advisory is the part of investment banking that advises companies on buying, selling or merging with other businesses. The adviser values the company, finds or approaches the other side, runs the process and helps negotiate the deal, in return for a fee.',
    'ma.faq.1.q': 'What is the difference between buy-side and sell-side?',
    'ma.faq.1.a': 'Sell-side means advising a company that is being sold: preparing the materials, finding buyers and running the auction. Buy-side means advising an acquirer: identifying targets, valuing them and helping structure and negotiate the offer.',
    'ma.faq.2.q': 'What does an M&A analyst do?',
    'ma.faq.2.a': 'Analysts build valuation and M&A models, run accretion and dilution analysis, prepare teasers and information memoranda, support due diligence and put together client presentations. It is analytical, detail-heavy work with long hours.',
    'ma.faq.3.q': 'How many hours do M&A bankers work?',
    'ma.faq.3.a': 'Junior bankers often work seventy to eighty hours a week, and analysts sometimes report close to a hundred hours during a busy deal, with late nights and weekends. Hours usually improve at more senior levels.',
    'ma.faq.4.q': 'What are the exit opportunities from M&A?',
    'ma.faq.4.a': 'Common moves are private equity, corporate development, equity research, venture and growth funds, and in-house strategy or finance roles. Many people also stay and build a long-term career in M&A.',
    'ma.faq.5.q': 'What skills do I need for M&A?',
    'ma.faq.5.a': 'Strong financial modelling, valuation and M&A modelling, a solid grasp of accounting and financial analysis, attention to detail, clear communication, negotiation sense and the ability to work under pressure.',
    'ma.faq.6.q': 'Do you need an MBA for M&A?',
    'ma.faq.6.a': 'Not to start as an analyst, which is usually filled straight from university. An MBA is the classic route into the associate level and can speed up progression.',
    'ma.faq.7.q': 'How do I get an M&A internship?',
    'ma.faq.7.a': 'Apply early through spring weeks and summer programmes, recruit at target universities, consider boutique advisers as a less crowded way in, network with bankers and alumni, and prepare hard for technical interviews.',
