    'pe.vs.0.t': 'Private equity vs investment banking',
    'pe.vs.0.d': 'Banking advises on deals and raises capital for clients. Private equity invests its own fund and owns the companies, so the focus shifts from execution to long-term value.',
    'pe.vs.1.t': 'Private equity vs venture capital',
    'pe.vs.1.d': 'Venture capital backs young, fast-growing companies with high risk. Private equity usually buys mature, profitable businesses and often uses debt.',
    'pe.vs.2.t': 'Private equity vs corporate finance',
    'pe.vs.2.d': 'Corporate finance sits inside a company and manages its funding and strategy. Private equity is on the investor side, buying and improving companies.',
    'pe.vs.3.t': 'Private equity vs asset management',
    'pe.vs.3.d': 'Asset management invests mainly in listed shares and bonds for many clients. Private equity invests in private companies over longer horizons.',
    'pe.vs.4.t': 'Private equity vs transaction services',
    'pe.vs.4.d': 'Transaction services checks the numbers behind a deal for a buyer. Private equity is the buyer, deciding whether and how to invest.',
    'pe.vs.5.t': 'Private equity vs corporate development',
    'pe.vs.5.d': 'Corporate development sits inside an operating company and looks for acquisitions that fit its parent\'s existing strategy. Private equity invests through an independent fund, buys businesses across many industries, and answers to fund investors rather than a single corporate parent.',
    'pe.vs.6.t': 'Private equity vs debt advisory',
    'pe.vs.6.d': 'Debt advisory helps companies and sponsors arrange the borrowing behind a transaction, without taking an ownership stake itself. Private equity is usually the client on the other side of that table, structuring that same debt into a deal it owns and has to service.',
