    'finsub.faq.text': 'Frequently asked questions about this career path are coming soon.',
    'finsub.card.soon': 'Coming soon',
    'finsub.ib.intro': 'Investment banking is about advising companies and governments on their largest financial decisions, from mergers and acquisitions to raising capital on public markets. Analysts build financial models, prepare client materials and support live transactions. It is one of the most demanding and best known routes into high finance.',
    'finsub.ma.intro': 'Mergers and acquisitions advisors guide companies through buying, selling and merging businesses. The work runs from the first strategic idea to valuation, negotiation and closing the deal. It combines financial analysis with commercial judgement and stakeholder management.',
    'finsub.cf.intro': 'Corporate finance covers how a company funds itself and allocates capital, from financing decisions to financial strategy and investor relations. Professionals work either inside a company or in an advisory role. The focus is on creating and protecting long-term value.',
    'finsub.pe.intro': 'Private equity firms buy companies, improve how they perform and sell them again for a return, usually over several years. Investment professionals analyse deals, work with management teams and think like long-term owners. It is a natural next step for many people who start in investment banking.',
    'finsub.vc.intro': 'Venture capital investors back early-stage companies with high growth potential, from the first funding rounds through to scale-up. The work combines spotting promising founders and markets with supporting portfolio companies as they grow. It sits at the intersection of finance, technology and entrepreneurship.',
    'finsub.am.intro': 'Asset managers invest and manage money on behalf of institutions and private clients, building portfolios across shares, bonds and other assets. Roles range from research and portfolio management to client work. Success is measured over the long term, against clear risk and return goals.',
    'finsub.er.intro': 'Equity research analysts study listed companies and sectors and publish views on whether their shares are attractive. The work is deeply analytical, combining financial modelling with industry knowledge and clear writing. It is a strong foundation for many other finance careers.',
    'finsub.cd.intro': 'Corporate development teams drive acquisitions, partnerships and strategic projects from within a company. They sit close to leadership and turn strategy into concrete deals and initiatives. The role blends the deal skills of banking with a long-term, in-house perspective.',
    'finsub.val.intro': 'Valuation specialists determine what companies, shares and assets are really worth, for transactions, financial reporting and disputes. The work relies on financial models, market data and professional judgement. It is central to almost every major financial decision.',
    'finsub.ts.intro': 'Transaction services teams run the financial due diligence behind acquisitions, checking the numbers before a deal closes. They analyse a target company in depth and flag risks and opportunities for buyers. It is a fast route into the world of deals.',
    'finsub.da.intro': 'Debt advisory professionals help companies raise, structure and refinance debt on the best possible terms. They work with banks, funds and other lenders to arrange financing that fits a client. It is a specialised corner of finance with clear, tangible outcomes.',
    'finsub.ref.intro': 'Real estate finance covers the funding and investment behind property, from single developments to large portfolios. Professionals analyse assets, structure financing and assess risk and return. It combines the discipline of finance with the tangible world of buildings.',
    'finsub.inf.intro': 'Infrastructure finance funds long-lived projects such as energy, transport and public utilities, often with a long-term investment horizon. The work involves complex financing structures and stable, predictable returns. It is increasingly linked to the energy transition and sustainability.',
    'finsub.fo.intro': 'Family offices manage the wealth and investments of high net worth families across many asset types. The work is broad, from investing and reporting to long-term planning. It offers a rare, all-round view of the investment world.',
    /* Finance hub */
