    'fin.intro.label': 'Introduction',
    'fin.intro.title': 'What is a career in finance?',
    'fin.intro.p1': 'A career in finance means helping companies, investors and institutions make decisions about money: raising capital, valuing businesses, structuring deals and managing investments. It spans advisory work at investment banks, buy-side roles at private equity and venture capital firms, and in-house positions in corporate finance teams.',
    'fin.intro.p2': 'Students choose finance for the steep learning curve, the exposure to high-stakes transactions and the clear path to responsibility early in their career. The work is analytical and demanding, and it opens doors across the entire business world.',
