    'com.roles.label': 'Roles',
    'com.roles.text': 'Each step up the ladder shifts the emphasis further from drafting contracts toward setting commercial strategy and managing the client relationship. Most lawyers climb this ladder at the same firm, though moving between firms or into a company at any level is common.',
    'com.roles.title': 'Roles in the commercial practice',
    'com.route.0.d': 'The most direct route, with courses that tie directly into the practice.',
    'com.route.0.t': 'Master\'s in corporate or private law',
    'com.route.1.d': 'Gaining practical experience at a firm or company before graduating.',
    'com.route.1.t': 'Internship during the master\'s',
    'com.route.2.d': 'Structured programmes in which you rotate through several practice groups.',
    'com.route.2.t': 'Traineeship after graduating',
    'com.route.3.d': 'Practising negotiation and contract drafting outside the regular curriculum.',
    'com.route.3.t': 'Moot courts on contract law',
    'com.route.4.d': 'A board or committee year at a law student association builds network and experience.',
    'com.route.4.t': 'Student associations and committees',
    'com.route.5.d': 'A case note or article on contract law stands out in applications.',
    'com.route.5.t': 'Publishing in legal journals',
    'com.route.6.d': 'A student role in a company\'s legal department gives insight from the other side of the table.',
    'com.route.6.t': 'Work experience at a company',
    'com.route.7.d': 'Coffee chats and alumni contacts open many doors when applying.',
    'com.route.7.t': 'Networking with lawyers and alumni',
    'com.routes.label': 'Getting in',
    'com.routes.text': 'Most routes run through a law master\'s with a specialisation in private law or corporate law, followed by an internship or traineeship at a firm or company. An affinity with how businesses operate is a plus, but not a requirement.',
    'com.routes.title': 'How you get into commercial',
