    'com.vs.0.d': 'Corporate/M&A structures the acquisition of a company itself. Commercial handles the ongoing trade contracts through which that company does business.',
    'com.vs.0.t': 'Commercial vs Corporate/M&A',
    'com.vs.1.d': 'Intellectual Property protects and registers rights such as trademarks and patents. Commercial records the terms on which others may use those rights.',
    'com.vs.1.t': 'Commercial vs Intellectual Property',
    'com.vs.2.d': 'Commercial drafts the contract. Dispute Resolution steps in once one of the parties fails to honour that contract.',
    'com.vs.2.t': 'Commercial vs Dispute Resolution',
    'com.vs.3.d': 'Antitrust assesses whether arrangements between businesses restrict competition. Commercial separately handles the substance of the trading relationship itself.',
    'com.vs.3.t': 'Commercial vs Antitrust, Competition & Trade',
    'com.vs.4.d': 'Employment governs the working relationship between an employer and employee. Commercial governs the trading relationship between two businesses.',
    'com.vs.4.t': 'Commercial vs Employment, Labour & Pensions',
    'com.vs.label': 'Compare',
    'com.vs.text': 'These practice areas often overlap in the same matters, which is why students sometimes mix them up. The distinction mainly lies in what exactly is being recorded or protected, and in which phase of the relationship the work takes place.',
    'com.vs.title': 'Commercial versus other practice areas',
