    'cma.comp.note': 'Ranges are general indications for the Dutch legal profession, not specific to this practice area or a particular firm. See the vacancy pages for concrete salary figures where a firm publishes them.',
    'cma.comp.p1': 'Compensation in the legal profession usually consists of a fixed salary that rises with seniority, and at some firms a variable bonus tied to individual and firm performance. Corporate/M&A does not differ materially in pay structure from other practice areas at the same firm.',
    'cma.comp.p2': 'The ranges below are general indications for larger Dutch and international firms, and do not apply specifically to this practice area or to any of the firms named on this page. Actual pay varies by firm, region and role, and is listed where known in the individual vacancies on this site.',
    'cma.comp.p3': 'From partner level, the nature of compensation changes. A partner typically shares in the firm\'s profits rather than receiving a fixed salary, which ties pay more closely to their own client portfolio and the results of the practice group as a whole.',
