    'cma.roles.label': 'Roles',
    'cma.roles.text': 'Each step up the ladder shifts the emphasis further from carrying out due diligence toward setting deal strategy and managing the client relationship. Most lawyers climb this ladder at the same firm, though moving between firms at any level is common.',
    'cma.roles.title': 'Roles in the corporate/M&A practice',
    'cma.route.0.d': 'The most direct route, with courses that tie directly into the practice.',
    'cma.route.0.t': 'Master\'s in corporate law',
    'cma.route.1.d': 'Gaining practical experience at a firm before graduating.',
    'cma.route.1.t': 'Internship during the master\'s',
    'cma.route.2.d': 'Structured programmes in which you rotate through several practice groups.',
    'cma.route.2.t': 'Traineeship after graduating',
    'cma.route.3.d': 'Practising negotiation and deal documentation outside the regular curriculum.',
    'cma.route.3.t': 'Moot courts on corporate law',
    'cma.route.4.d': 'A board or committee year at a law student association builds network and experience.',
    'cma.route.4.t': 'Student associations and committees',
    'cma.route.5.d': 'A case note or article on corporate law stands out in applications.',
    'cma.route.5.t': 'Publishing in legal journals',
    'cma.route.6.d': 'A student role gives insight from the other side of the table.',
    'cma.route.6.t': 'Work experience in a corporate department',
    'cma.route.7.d': 'Coffee chats and alumni contacts open many doors when applying.',
    'cma.route.7.t': 'Networking with lawyers and alumni',
    'cma.routes.label': 'Getting in',
    'cma.routes.text': 'Most routes run through a law master\'s with a specialisation in corporate law, followed by an internship or traineeship at a firm. An affinity with deal work and numbers is a plus, but not a requirement.',
    'cma.routes.title': 'How you get into corporate/M&A',
    'cma.skill.0': 'Analytical thinking',
    'cma.skill.1': 'Precise writing',
    'cma.skill.2': 'Commercial judgement',
    'cma.skill.3': 'Attention to detail',
    'cma.skill.4': 'Negotiation',
    'cma.skill.5': 'Project management',
    'cma.skill.6': 'Client focus',
    'cma.skill.7': 'Working under deadlines',
    'cma.skill.8': 'Legal English',
    'cma.skill.9': 'Persuasiveness',
    'cma.skills.label': 'Skills',
    'cma.skills.text': 'Legal knowledge gets the most attention in training, but the lawyers who stay longest often stand out through commercial judgement: understanding what the client is really trying to achieve with a transaction, not just what the contract literally says.',
    'cma.skills.title': 'Skills you will need',
    'cma.sub': 'Discover what corporate/M&A means in legal practice: how lawyers guide mergers and acquisitions, what they do day to day, the career ladder, and how students prepare for an internship or traineeship.',
    'cma.tier.0.d': 'Firms that guide large, often cross-border acquisitions and IPOs.',
    'cma.tier.0.t': 'International firm',
    'cma.tier.1.d': 'A corporate/M&A practice that often forms the core of the firm, alongside banking & finance and dispute resolution.',
    'cma.tier.1.t': 'Dutch full-service firm',
    'cma.tier.2.d': 'Smaller, often specialised teams that serve the SME segment and mid-sized transactions.',
    'cma.tier.2.t': 'Boutique or regional firm',
    'cma.tier.label': 'The practice',
    'cma.tier.text': 'The breakdown below mainly says something about the scale and type of transaction you work on, not about the quality of the work.',
    'cma.tier.text2': 'At international firms you work on large, often cross-border deals with dozens of advisors at once. At Dutch full-service firms, corporate/M&A often forms the core of the practice, with a strong link to banking and finance. At boutique and regional firms you work on smaller-scale, often domestic transactions, taking on more responsibility earlier in your career.',
    'cma.tier.title': 'Three settings where you practise this field',
    'cma.tl.label': 'Career timeline',
    'cma.tl.p1': 'The legal profession has a fixed statutory basis for the first step: a traineeship in the Netherlands generally lasts three years and is mandatory for every starting lawyer, regardless of practice area. After that, the pace of progression depends heavily on the firm and on individual performance.',
    'cma.tl.p2': 'After the traineeship, the emphasis shifts from carrying out due diligence to independently leading transactions. Making partner takes more than ten years of legal experience at most firms, and is often accompanied by a formal nomination by the existing partners.',
    'cma.tl.p3': 'Not everyone climbs the whole ladder at the same firm. Some lawyers move into business after a few years, for example as in-house counsel in a company\'s corporate department.',
    'cma.tl.th1': 'Level',
    'cma.tl.th2': 'Typical time in role',
    'cma.tl.title': 'How long each step takes',
    'cma.tl.y1': '3 years, mandatory by law',
    'cma.tl.y2': '3 to 5 years',
    'cma.tl.y3': '2 to 4 years',
    'cma.tl.y4': 'top level, 10+ years in total',
    'cma.vac.all': 'View all vacancies',
    'cma.vac.label': 'Vacancies',
    'cma.vac.text': 'We only show real, current openings with a link to the employer. Internships, traineeships and lawyer roles appear here. In the meantime, browse all current vacancies.',
    'cma.vac.title': 'Corporate/M&A vacancies',
    'cma.vs.0.d': 'Corporate/M&A structures the acquisition itself. Banking & finance arranges the loan the buyer uses to pay for that acquisition.',
    'cma.vs.0.t': 'Corporate/M&A vs Banking & Finance',
    'cma.vs.1.d': 'Corporate/M&A handles the one-off acquisition of a company. Commercial handles the ongoing trade contracts through which that company does business.',
    'cma.vs.1.t': 'Corporate/M&A vs Commercial',
    'cma.vs.2.d': 'Antitrust assesses whether an acquisition harms competition. Corporate/M&A separately structures the transaction itself.',
    'cma.vs.2.t': 'Corporate/M&A vs Antitrust, Competition & Trade',
    'cma.vs.3.d': 'Tax law assesses the tax consequences of a transaction structure. Corporate/M&A handles the underlying purchase agreement itself.',
    'cma.vs.3.t': 'Corporate/M&A vs Tax',
    'cma.vs.4.d': 'Corporate/M&A guides the healthy sale of a company. Restructuring & Insolvency steps in once a company is in financial difficulty.',
    'cma.vs.4.t': 'Corporate/M&A vs Restructuring & Insolvency',
    'cma.vs.label': 'Compare',
    'cma.vs.text': 'These practice areas often overlap in the same matters, which is why students sometimes mix them up. The distinction mainly lies in what exactly is being arranged, and in which phase of the transaction the work takes place.',
    'cma.vs.title': 'Corporate/M&A versus other practice areas',
    'cma.w1.d': 'The practice area covering the purchase, sale and legal structure of companies.',
    'cma.w1.t': 'What it is',
