    'elp.badge': 'Legal career path',
    'elp.h1': 'Employment, Labour & Pensions',
    'elp.sub': 'Discover what employment, labour & pensions means in legal practice: how lawyers guide employment relationships, works councils and pension schemes, what they do day to day, the career ladder, and how students prepare for an internship or traineeship.',
    'elp.cta.vac': 'View vacancies',
    'elp.cta.paths': 'Explore legal paths',
    'elp.intro.label': 'Introduction',
    'elp.intro.title': 'What is employment, labour & pensions?',
    'elp.intro.p': 'Employment, labour & pensions is the practice area centred on the relationship between employer and employee: from drafting an employment contract to guiding a dismissal, and from employee representation within a company to the pension scheme that goes with it.',
    'elp.intro.p2': 'The field combines individual employment law, such as contracts and dismissal proceedings, with collective labour law, such as collective bargaining and the role of the works council. Pensions law is an additional specialism often housed within the same practice group.',
    'elp.intro.p3': 'Employer-side lawyers advise companies on their workforce policy, while in reorganisations and acquisitions this practice area works closely with corporate/M&A and restructuring & insolvency.',
    'elp.w1.t': 'What it is',
    'elp.w1.d': 'The practice area covering the relationship between employer and employee, from contract to pension.',
    'elp.w2.t': 'What it centres on',
    'elp.w2.d': 'Advising on employment terms, dismissal, employee representation and pension schemes.',
    'elp.w3.t': 'Why clients need it',
    'elp.w3.d': 'To ground workforce policy legally and to prevent or resolve employment disputes.',
    'elp.w4.t': 'Why students find it attractive',
    'elp.w4.d': 'Direct human contact, broad social relevance, and a mix of advisory work and litigation.',
    'elp.tier.label': 'The practice',
    'elp.tier.title': 'Three settings where you practise this field',
    'elp.tier.text': 'The breakdown below mainly says something about the type of client and the scale of matters, not about the quality of the work.',
    'elp.tier.0.t': 'Dutch full-service firm',
    'elp.tier.0.d': 'An employment law practice alongside other practice groups, often brought in during reorganisations and acquisitions.',
    'elp.tier.1.t': 'Boutique firm specialised in employment law',
    'elp.tier.1.d': 'Firms fully focused on employment law, often with deep specialisation in complex dismissal matters.',
    'elp.tier.2.t': 'Regional firm or legal expense insurer',
    'elp.tier.2.d': 'Handles a high volume of individual employment matters, often on behalf of employees or SMEs.',
    'elp.tier.text2': 'At Dutch full-service firms, the employment practice often sits close to corporate/M&A, since acquisitions and reorganisations affect staff. Boutique firms specialise fully in employment law and build deep expertise as a result. At a regional firm or legal expense insurer, you handle a larger volume of individual matters, often on behalf of employees.',
    'elp.do.label': 'What they do',
    'elp.do.title': 'What employment lawyers do',
    'elp.do.text': 'The work differs by matter, but the building blocks below come up in almost every employment law question.',
    'elp.do.0.t': 'Drafting and reviewing employment contracts',
    'elp.do.0.d': 'Structuring individual employment agreements and terms of employment.',
    'elp.do.1.t': 'Guiding dismissal proceedings',
    'elp.do.1.d': 'Preparing and conducting a termination of employment via the UWV or the sub-district court.',
    'elp.do.2.t': 'Negotiating reorganisations and social plans',
    'elp.do.2.d': 'Aligning collective redundancy and its conditions with trade unions and the works council.',
    'elp.do.3.t': 'Advising on employee representation',
    'elp.do.3.d': 'Advising companies on the role and rights of the works council.',
    'elp.do.4.t': 'Advising on pension schemes',
    'elp.do.4.d': 'Advising employers and pension funds on the design and amendment of pension schemes.',
    'elp.do.5.t': 'Supporting collective bargaining',
    'elp.do.5.d': 'Guiding employers through the negotiation of collective labour agreements.',
    'elp.do.6.t': 'Handling employment disputes',
    'elp.do.6.d': 'Assessing disputes over performance, integrity or terms of employment.',
    'elp.do.7.t': 'Guiding labour migration',
    'elp.do.7.d': 'Advising employers on employing staff from abroad.',
