    'elp.dp.text2': 'Who does which step depends on seniority. Junior lawyers build the file and work out submissions in detail, while senior lawyers negotiate and discuss procedural risks with the client.',
    'elp.dp.text3': 'Not every proceeding ends in a ruling: parties can still reach a settlement agreement at any point, which is often faster and more certain than litigating all the way through a possible appeal.',
