    'elp.faq.label': 'FAQ',
    'elp.faq.title': 'Frequently asked questions',
    'elp.faq.0.q': 'What is employment, labour & pensions?',
    'elp.faq.0.a': 'Employment, labour & pensions is the practice area centred on the relationship between employer and employee, from employment contracts and dismissal to employee representation and pension schemes.',
    'elp.faq.1.q': 'What is the difference between individual and collective labour law?',
    'elp.faq.1.a': 'Individual labour law concerns the relationship between one employer and one employee, such as an employment contract or dismissal. Collective labour law concerns agreements that apply to larger groups of employees, such as a collective labour agreement or the role of the works council.',
    'elp.faq.2.q': 'What does an employment lawyer do day to day?',
    'elp.faq.2.a': 'Employment lawyers draft employment contracts, guide dismissal proceedings, advise on employee representation and pension schemes, support collective bargaining, and handle employment disputes.',
    'elp.faq.3.q': 'What is the Balanced Labour Market Act (WAB)?',
    'elp.faq.3.a': 'The WAB is a law that governs the balance between permanent and flexible employment contracts and the associated dismissal routes. It has been amended regularly and remains a key point of attention in employment law practice.',
    'elp.faq.4.q': 'What is the role of the works council?',
    'elp.faq.4.a': 'The works council represents staff and has advisory and consent rights over major employer decisions, such as reorganisations, set out in the Works Councils Act.',
    'elp.faq.5.q': 'What does pensions law involve within this field?',
    'elp.faq.5.a': 'Pensions law concerns the legal design, administration and amendment of pension schemes, and is often handled within the same practice group as employment law.',
    'elp.faq.6.q': 'What skills do you need for this field?',
    'elp.faq.6.a': 'Precise writing, negotiation skills, people skills, attention to detail, and the ability to work under the pressure of procedural deadlines.',
    'elp.faq.7.q': 'How do I get into this field as a student?',
    'elp.faq.7.a': 'Take electives in employment law, do an internship at a firm or HR department, and apply to structured traineeships that offer a rotation in this field.',
    'elp.rel.label': 'Related',
    'elp.rel.title': 'Related legal paths',
    'elp.end.title': 'Start your journey in employment, labour & pensions',
