    'esg.badge': 'Legal career path',
    'esg.h1': 'ESG',
    'esg.sub': 'Discover what ESG (Environmental, Social, Governance) means in legal practice: how lawyers guide companies through sustainability regulation, human rights and corporate governance, what they do day to day, the career ladder, and how students prepare for an internship or traineeship.',
    'esg.cta.vac': 'View vacancies',
    'esg.cta.paths': 'Explore legal paths',
    'esg.intro.label': 'Introduction',
    'esg.intro.title': 'What is ESG in legal practice?',
    'esg.intro.p': 'ESG stands for Environmental, Social and Governance and, in legal practice, is the field centred on regulation around sustainability, human rights in the supply chain, and good corporate governance. It is not a single code of law, but a fast-growing body of regulation that increasingly affects companies directly.',
    'esg.intro.p2': 'The E stands for environment and climate, the S for human rights and working conditions in the supply chain, and the G for how a company is governed and overseen. Lawyers in this field help companies meet the reporting and due diligence obligations that flow from these three themes.',
    'esg.intro.p3': 'ESG lawyers often work with other practice groups: an ESG issue in an acquisition touches corporate/M&A, a climate dispute touches dispute resolution, and the social side of ESG touches employment, labour & pensions.',
    'esg.w1.t': 'What it is',
    'esg.w1.d': 'The practice area covering sustainability regulation, supply chain human rights and corporate governance.',
    'esg.w2.t': 'What it centres on',
    'esg.w2.d': 'Advising on reporting obligations, supply chain responsibility and governance structures.',
    'esg.w3.t': 'Why clients need it',
    'esg.w3.d': 'To comply with fast-growing European and Dutch sustainability legislation.',
    'esg.w4.t': 'Why students find it attractive',
    'esg.w4.d': 'A new and fast-changing field with direct social relevance.',
    'esg.tier.label': 'The practice',
    'esg.tier.title': 'Three settings where you practise this field',
    'esg.tier.text': 'The breakdown below mainly says something about the type of client and ESG issue, not about the quality of the work.',
    'esg.tier.0.t': 'International firm',
    'esg.tier.0.d': 'Firms that guide multinationals through cross-border sustainability regulation.',
    'esg.tier.1.t': 'Dutch full-service firm',
    'esg.tier.1.d': 'ESG advice often integrated into the corporate or governance practice, in acquisitions and annual reporting.',
    'esg.tier.2.t': 'Specialised advisory firm',
    'esg.tier.2.d': 'Firms fully focused on sustainability reporting and compliance, often working alongside lawyers.',
    'esg.tier.text2': 'At international firms you often work on cross-border sustainability issues for multinationals. At Dutch full-service firms, ESG advice often sits close to the corporate or governance practice. Specialised advisory firms focus entirely on sustainability reporting and compliance, often in close cooperation with lawyers.',
    'esg.do.label': 'What they do',
    'esg.do.title': 'What ESG lawyers do',
    'esg.do.text': 'The work differs by assignment, but the building blocks below come up in almost every ESG matter.',
    'esg.do.0.t': 'Advising on sustainability reporting',
    'esg.do.0.d': 'Guiding companies through European reporting obligations.',
    'esg.do.1.t': 'Human rights and environmental due diligence',
    'esg.do.1.d': 'Screening a company\'s supply chain for human rights and environmental risks.',
    'esg.do.2.t': 'Advising on corporate governance',
    'esg.do.2.d': 'Advising boards on responsibilities, oversight and stakeholder interests.',
    'esg.do.3.t': 'Assessing climate risk',
    'esg.do.3.d': 'Mapping transition risk and liability risk related to climate change.',
    'esg.do.4.t': 'Reviewing sustainability claims',
    'esg.do.4.d': 'Assessing marketing statements for the risk of misleading sustainability claims.',
    'esg.do.5.t': 'Drafting ESG clauses',
    'esg.do.5.d': 'Setting out sustainability commitments in contracts and financing agreements.',
    'esg.do.6.t': 'Setting up compliance programmes',
    'esg.do.6.d': 'Designing internal processes that let a company meet ESG legislation.',
    'esg.do.7.t': 'Coordinating with other practice groups',
    'esg.do.7.d': 'Working with corporate, employment and dispute resolution when a matter overlaps.',
    'esg.law.label': 'Legal framework',
    'esg.law.title': 'The key legislation',
    'esg.law.text': 'ESG revolves around a fast-growing set of European and Dutch rules that keep recurring, even though application differs greatly from company to company.',
    'esg.law.0.t': 'Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive (CSRD)',
    'esg.law.0.d': 'EU directive requiring large companies to produce extensive sustainability reporting.',
    'esg.law.1.t': 'Corporate Sustainability Due Diligence Directive (CSDDD)',
    'esg.law.1.d': 'EU directive requiring companies to carry out human rights and environmental due diligence in the supply chain.',
    'esg.law.2.t': 'EU Taxonomy Regulation',
    'esg.law.2.d': 'Classifies which economic activities count as environmentally sustainable.',
    'esg.law.3.t': 'Sustainable Finance Disclosure Regulation (SFDR)',
    'esg.law.3.d': 'Requires financial market participants to disclose sustainability risks.',
    'esg.law.4.t': 'Book 2 of the Dutch Civil Code',
    'esg.law.4.d': 'Contains the provisions on management, supervision and accountability within legal entities.',
    'esg.law.5.t': 'Dutch Corporate Governance Code',
    'esg.law.5.d': 'Contains principles and best practices for the good governance of listed companies.',
    'esg.div.label': 'Practice areas',
    'esg.div.title': 'The main sub-areas',
    'esg.div.text': 'ESG is broad, and most lawyers specialise within one of the sub-areas below.',
    'esg.div.0.t': 'Sustainability reporting',
    'esg.div.0.d': 'Advice on CSRD reporting obligations and the underlying data.',
    'esg.div.1.t': 'Human rights and supply chain responsibility',
    'esg.div.1.d': 'Due diligence on working conditions and human rights at suppliers.',
    'esg.div.2.t': 'Climate and environment',
    'esg.div.2.d': 'Climate-related disputes, permits and environmental regulation.',
    'esg.div.3.t': 'Corporate governance',
    'esg.div.3.d': 'Governance structures, oversight and the interests of different stakeholders.',
    'esg.div.4.t': 'Sustainable finance',
    'esg.div.4.d': 'Green bonds and loans with sustainability-linked terms.',
    'esg.dp.label': 'Step by step',
    'esg.dp.title': 'How a CSRD reporting cycle unfolds',
    'esg.dp.text': 'Most sustainability reporting cycles follow a similar path, from the materiality assessment to publication. At more complex companies, gathering data can take considerable time.',
    'esg.dp.text2': 'Who does which step depends on seniority. Junior lawyers map the underlying regulation and data, while senior lawyers set the reporting strategy and advise the board.',
    'esg.dp.text3': 'Not every cycle runs smoothly: an incomplete materiality assessment or missing data can cause delays further down the process, which often costs more time than careful preparation upfront.',
    'esg.dp.0': 'Materiality assessment',
    'esg.dp.1': 'Data gathering',
    'esg.dp.2': 'Report drafting',
    'esg.dp.3': 'Auditor assurance',
    'esg.dp.4': 'Annual report publication',
    'esg.dp.5': 'Oversight and enforcement',
    'esg.dp.caption': 'A simplified overview of a CSRD reporting cycle: the materiality assessment, gathering data, drafting the report, auditor assurance, publication in the annual report, and oversight afterwards.',
    'esg.roles.label': 'Roles',
    'esg.roles.title': 'Roles in the ESG practice',
    'esg.roles.text': 'Each step up the ladder shifts the emphasis further from mapping regulation toward setting ESG strategy and advising the board. Most lawyers climb this ladder at the same firm, though moving between firms at any level is common.',
    'esg.role.tasks': 'Key tasks',
    'esg.role.skills': 'Core skills',
