    'esg.tl.p1': 'The legal profession has a fixed statutory basis for the first step: a traineeship in the Netherlands generally lasts three years and is mandatory for every starting lawyer, regardless of practice area. After that, the pace of progression depends heavily on the firm and on individual performance.',
    'esg.tl.p2': 'After the traineeship, the emphasis shifts from mapping regulation to independently advising on ESG strategy. Making partner takes more than ten years of legal experience at most firms.',
    'esg.tl.p3': 'Not everyone climbs the whole ladder at the same firm. Some lawyers move into an in-house sustainability role at a company, bringing their ESG experience with them.',
