    'esg.comp.note': 'Ranges are general indications for the Dutch legal profession, not specific to this practice area or a particular firm. See the vacancy pages for concrete salary figures where a firm publishes them.',
    'esg.day.label': 'A day in the life',
    'esg.day.title': 'A typical day for a junior lawyer',
    'esg.day.p1': 'The day often starts with reviewing new or amended regulation or preparing advice on a reporting obligation. On days without a client meeting, much of the time goes into drafting compliance documents and searching through source data.',
    'esg.day.p2': 'An ESG lawyer often works on several matters at once, from a reporting cycle to a supply chain due diligence. That requires strict planning, since ESG legislation changes fast and deadlines are often set at EU level.',
    'esg.day.p3': 'On a day with a client meeting, the pace shifts entirely. The lawyer prepares the advice, anticipates questions from the board, and explains complex regulation in plain terms.',
    'esg.ia.label': 'Juniors',
    'esg.ia.title': 'What trainee lawyers do',
    'esg.ia.text': 'Junior lawyers carry much of the research and drafting work an ESG opinion rests on, under the supervision of a supervising partner.',
    'esg.ia.text2': 'Much of this work goes back and forth several times between trainee and supervisor before advice is sent. That repetition is not inefficiency, it is how a junior lawyer learns which regulation in an ESG matter really matters.',
