    'esg.iad.6': 'Sitting in on client meetings',
    'esg.iad.7': 'Correspondence with regulators',
    'esg.skills.label': 'Skills',
    'esg.skills.title': 'Skills you will need',
    'esg.skills.text': 'Legal knowledge gets the most attention in training, but the lawyers who stay longest often stand out through analytical ability: being able to translate fast-changing regulation into concrete, workable advice.',
    'esg.skill.0': 'Analytical thinking',
    'esg.skill.1': 'Precise writing',
    'esg.skill.2': 'Persuasiveness',
    'esg.skill.3': 'Attention to detail',
    'esg.skill.4': 'Adaptability',
    'esg.skill.5': 'Resilience under pressure',
    'esg.skill.6': 'Client focus',
    'esg.skill.7': 'Working under deadlines',
    'esg.skill.8': 'Perseverance',
    'esg.skill.9': 'Strategic judgement',
    'esg.routes.label': 'Getting in',
    'esg.routes.title': 'How you get into ESG',
    'esg.routes.text': 'Most routes run through a law master\'s with a specialisation in corporate law or environmental law, followed by an internship or traineeship at a firm. An affinity with sustainability and regulation is a plus.',
    'esg.route.0.t': 'Master\'s in corporate law or environmental law',
    'esg.route.0.d': 'The most direct route, with courses that tie directly into the practice.',
    'esg.route.1.t': 'Internship during the master\'s',
    'esg.route.1.d': 'Gaining practical experience at a firm before graduating.',
    'esg.route.2.t': 'Traineeship after graduating',
    'esg.route.2.d': 'Structured programmes in which you rotate through several practice groups.',
    'esg.route.3.t': 'Courses on sustainability law',
    'esg.route.3.d': 'Advanced electives show affinity with the broader field.',
    'esg.route.4.t': 'Student associations and committees',
    'esg.route.4.d': 'A board or committee year at a student association builds network and experience.',
    'esg.route.5.t': 'Publishing in legal journals',
    'esg.route.5.d': 'A case note or article on sustainability law stands out in applications.',
    'esg.route.6.t': 'Work experience at a sustainability department',
    'esg.route.6.d': 'An internship at a company\'s sustainability department gives insight from the client side.',
    'esg.route.7.t': 'Networking with lawyers and alumni',
    'esg.route.7.d': 'Coffee chats and alumni contacts open many doors when applying.',
    'esg.prep.label': 'Preparation',
    'esg.prep.title': 'How to prepare as a student',
    'esg.prep.text': 'Preparation works best when it starts well before the application. Firms test not only legal knowledge, but also whether someone can follow fast-changing regulation and explain it clearly.',
    'esg.prep.0.t': 'Take courses in sustainability law and corporate law',
    'esg.prep.0.d': 'Build a solid grounding in regulation around sustainability and corporate governance.',
    'esg.prep.1.t': 'Read up on the CSRD and CSDDD',
    'esg.prep.1.d': 'Follow how these European directives are implemented and applied.',
    'esg.prep.2.t': 'Do a relevant internship',
    'esg.prep.2.d': 'Any internship at a firm or sustainability department strengthens your application.',
    'esg.prep.3.t': 'Practise interviews',
    'esg.prep.3.d': 'Prepare for questions on motivation, case studies and current affairs.',
    'esg.prep.4.t': 'Build a one-page CV',
    'esg.prep.4.d': 'Keep it clear and focused on relevant experience and results.',
    'esg.prep.5.t': 'Network early',
    'esg.prep.5.d': 'Reach out to lawyers and alumni before application rounds open.',
    'esg.prep.6.t': 'Follow developments in sustainability regulation',
    'esg.prep.6.d': 'New European directives follow each other quickly in this field.',
    'esg.prep.7.t': 'Improve your English',
    'esg.prep.7.d': 'European regulation and international clients often require work in English.',
    'esg.vs.label': 'Compare',
    'esg.vs.title': 'ESG versus other practice areas',
    'esg.vs.text': 'These practice areas often overlap in the same matters, which is why students sometimes mix them up. The distinction mainly lies in which part of the company or dispute is at the centre.',
    'esg.vs.0.t': 'ESG vs Corporate/M&A',
    'esg.vs.0.d': 'Corporate/M&A guides the transaction itself. ESG assesses the sustainability and governance risks that come with that transaction.',
    'esg.vs.1.t': 'ESG vs Commercial',
    'esg.vs.1.d': 'Commercial drafts the contract. ESG tests whether the sustainability claims and clauses within it hold up.',
    'esg.vs.2.t': 'ESG vs Administrative Law',
    'esg.vs.2.d': 'Administrative Law handles disputes with the government, for example over environmental permits. ESG advises more broadly on sustainability regulation towards the company itself.',
    'esg.vs.3.t': 'ESG vs Employment, Labour & Pensions',
    'esg.vs.3.d': 'Employment covers the employment relationship itself. ESG covers a company\'s broader social responsibility across its supply chain.',
    'esg.vs.4.t': 'ESG vs Dispute Resolution',
    'esg.vs.4.d': 'Dispute Resolution conducts the proceeding once a climate or sustainability dispute escalates. ESG focuses on preventing that through compliance.',
    'esg.emp.label': 'Employers',
    'esg.emp.title': 'Firms with an ESG practice in the Netherlands',
    'esg.emp.text': 'We only name firms here whose specific ESG practice has been verified. At this time, we have not yet been able to confirm a firm for this practice area.',
    'esg.emp.soon': 'We are working on verifying firms with a specific ESG practice in the Netherlands. In the meantime, browse all employers or all open vacancies.',
    'esg.emp.allcompanies': 'Browse all employers',
    'esg.vac.label': 'Vacancies',
