    'pp.faq.label': 'FAQ',
    'pp.faq.title': 'Frequently asked questions',
    'pp.faq.0.q': 'What is public procurement?',
    'pp.faq.0.a': 'Public procurement is the practice area setting the rules for how governments and other contracting authorities purchase works, supplies and services.',
    'pp.faq.1.q': 'Why does procurement law exist?',
    'pp.faq.1.a': 'Procurement law ensures fair, transparent and non-discriminatory access to public contracts, so that businesses from across the EU can compete on equal terms.',
    'pp.faq.2.q': 'What does a procurement lawyer do day to day?',
    'pp.faq.2.a': 'Procurement lawyers set up tender procedures, draft tender documents, assess bids, conduct summary proceedings against award decisions, and advise on the duty to tender.',
    'pp.faq.3.q': 'What is a standstill period?',
    'pp.faq.3.a': 'The standstill period is the mandatory waiting time between the provisional and final award, during which a rejected bidder can challenge the award decision, for example in summary proceedings.',
    'pp.faq.4.q': 'What is the difference between classic sectors and utilities sectors?',
    'pp.faq.4.a': 'Classic sectors concern regular public contracts for works, supplies and services. Utilities sectors concern tenders in water, energy, transport and postal services, with their own EU directive and partly different rules.',
    'pp.faq.5.q': 'What is the Committee of Procurement Experts?',
    'pp.faq.5.a': 'The Committee of Procurement Experts handles complaints about tender procedures as a low-threshold alternative to going to court.',
    'pp.faq.6.q': 'What skills do you need for public procurement?',
    'pp.faq.6.a': 'Precise writing, analytical thinking, procedural instinct, attention to detail, and the ability to work under the pressure of tight tender deadlines.',
    'pp.faq.7.q': 'How do I get into this field as a student?',
    'pp.faq.7.a': 'Take electives in administrative law or European law, do an internship at a firm or contracting authority, and apply to structured traineeships that offer a rotation in this field.',
    'pp.rel.label': 'Related',
    'pp.rel.title': 'Related legal paths',
    'pp.end.title': 'Start your journey in public procurement',
