    're.faq.label': 'FAQ',
    're.faq.title': 'Frequently asked questions',
    're.faq.0.q': 'What is real estate law?',
    're.faq.0.a': 'Real estate law is the practice area centred on the purchase, sale, lease, financing and development of property.',
    're.faq.1.q': 'What is the difference between leasing residential and commercial space?',
    're.faq.1.a': 'Leasing residential space carries extensive tenant protection, for example around rent and termination. Leasing commercial space follows its own, partly different rules, giving parties more freedom to agree terms themselves.',
    're.faq.2.q': 'What does a real estate lawyer do day to day?',
    're.faq.2.a': 'Real estate lawyers draft purchase and lease agreements, carry out due diligence, advise on financing and area development, and handle property disputes.',
    're.faq.3.q': 'What is a letter of intent in a property transaction?',
    're.faq.3.a': 'A letter of intent sets out the key agreements and process before parties enter into the final purchase agreement, often including agreements on exclusivity and the due diligence period.',
    're.faq.4.q': 'What does the Environment and Planning Act govern for property projects?',
    're.faq.4.a': 'The Environment and Planning Act bundles the rules for the physical environment, including construction, zoning plans and environmental permits relevant to area development.',
    're.faq.5.q': 'What is the Municipal Pre-emption Rights Act?',
    're.faq.5.a': 'This act gives municipalities, under certain conditions, the right to buy a designated plot first before the owner may sell it to another party.',
    're.faq.6.q': 'What skills do you need for real estate?',
    're.faq.6.a': 'Precise writing, negotiation skills, commercial awareness, attention to detail, and the ability to work under the pressure of transaction deadlines.',
    're.faq.7.q': 'How do I get into this field as a student?',
    're.faq.7.a': 'Take electives in property law and tenancy law, do an internship at a firm or property investor, and apply to structured traineeships that offer a rotation in this field.',
    're.rel.label': 'Related',
    're.rel.title': 'Related legal paths',
    're.end.title': 'Start your journey in real estate',
    're.end.sub': 'Browse open vacancies or discover the other legal career paths.',
    'ri.badge': 'Legal career path',
    'ri.h1': 'Restructuring & Insolvency',
    'ri.sub': 'Discover what restructuring & insolvency means in legal practice: how lawyers guide financially distressed companies, insolvency practitioners and creditors, what they do day to day, the career ladder, and how students prepare for an internship or traineeship.',
    'ri.cta.vac': 'View vacancies',
    'ri.cta.paths': 'Explore legal paths',
    'ri.intro.label': 'Introduction',
    'ri.intro.title': 'What is restructuring & insolvency?',
    'ri.intro.p': 'Restructuring & insolvency is the practice area centred on companies in financial distress: from restructuring outside formal insolvency to formal bankruptcy. It combines civil law, corporate law and procedural law in matters where speed and certainty are often decisive.',
    'ri.intro.p2': 'Since the introduction of the Dutch Act on Court Confirmation of Private Restructuring Plans (WHOA), companies can also reach a binding agreement with creditors outside formal insolvency. Formal bankruptcy law also remains relevant, with a central role for the insolvency practitioner who administers the bankrupt estate.',
    'ri.intro.p3': 'Lawyers in this field often work with other practice groups: a restructuring often touches employment law because of staff, banking & finance because of security interests, and dispute resolution once a conflict escalates.',
    'ri.w1.t': 'What it is',
    'ri.w1.d': 'The practice area covering companies in financial distress, from restructuring to bankruptcy.',
    'ri.w2.t': 'What it centres on',
    'ri.w2.d': 'Protecting the interests of creditors, shareholders and the company itself.',
    'ri.w3.t': 'Why clients need it',
    'ri.w3.d': 'To resolve financial distress in a controlled way or to wind down a bankruptcy in an orderly manner.',
    'ri.w4.t': 'Why students find it attractive',
    'ri.w4.d': 'Fast, high-pressure matters with direct consequences for a company and its staff.',
    'ri.tier.label': 'The practice',
    'ri.tier.title': 'Three settings where you practise this field',
    'ri.tier.text': 'The breakdown below mainly says something about the type of matter and the client you serve, not about the quality of the work.',
    'ri.tier.0.t': 'International firm',
    'ri.tier.0.d': 'Firms that handle large, often cross-border restructurings and insolvencies.',
    'ri.tier.1.t': 'Dutch full-service firm',
    'ri.tier.1.d': 'An insolvency practice alongside other practice groups, often brought in once a matter deteriorates.',
    'ri.tier.2.t': 'Boutique firm specialised in insolvency law',
    'ri.tier.2.d': 'Firms fully focused on restructuring and bankruptcy law, often holding many insolvency practitioner appointments.',
    'ri.tier.text2': 'At international firms you often work on large, cross-border restructurings. At Dutch full-service firms, the insolvency practice often sits close to corporate/M&A and banking & finance. Boutique firms specialise fully in insolvency law and often serve as insolvency practitioners themselves.',
    'ri.do.label': 'What they do',
    'ri.do.title': 'What restructuring & insolvency lawyers do',
    'ri.do.text': 'The work differs by matter, but the building blocks below come up in almost every insolvency matter.',
    'ri.do.0.t': 'Drafting restructuring plans',
    'ri.do.0.d': 'Drafting a WHOA plan to put a restructuring outside formal insolvency to creditors.',
    'ri.do.1.t': 'Assisting insolvency practitioners',
    'ri.do.1.d': 'Advising and assisting the insolvency practitioner in administering a bankruptcy.',
    'ri.do.2.t': 'Advising creditors',
    'ri.do.2.d': 'Advising creditors on their position and rights in a bankruptcy or restructuring.',
    'ri.do.3.t': 'Guiding suspension of payments',
    'ri.do.3.d': 'Guiding a company through a temporary suspension of payments to creditors.',
    'ri.do.4.t': 'Distressed company due diligence',
    'ri.do.4.d': 'Assessing the financial and legal risks of acquiring a distressed company.',
    'ri.do.5.t': 'Assessing director liability',
    'ri.do.5.d': 'Assessing whether directors are personally liable for damages in a bankruptcy.',
    'ri.do.6.t': 'Analysing security positions',
    'ri.do.6.d': 'Assessing and enforcing the position of pledgees and mortgagees in a bankruptcy.',
    'ri.do.7.t': 'Coordinating with other practice groups',
    'ri.do.7.d': 'Working with employment, banking & finance and dispute resolution when a matter overlaps.',
    'ri.law.label': 'Legal framework',
    'ri.law.title': 'The key legislation',
    'ri.law.text': 'Restructuring & insolvency revolves around a set of core statutes that keep recurring, even though application differs greatly between restructuring and formal bankruptcy.',
    'ri.law.0.t': 'Dutch Bankruptcy Act',
    'ri.law.0.d': 'Governs bankruptcy, suspension of payments, and the role of the insolvency practitioner.',
    'ri.law.1.t': 'Act on Court Confirmation of Private Restructuring Plans (WHOA)',
    'ri.law.1.d': 'Governs the binding plan a company can use to bind creditors outside formal insolvency.',
    'ri.law.2.t': 'Book 2 of the Dutch Civil Code',
    'ri.law.2.d': 'Contains the provisions on director liability for manifestly improper management.',
    'ri.law.3.t': 'Book 3 of the Dutch Civil Code',
    'ri.law.3.d': 'Governs security rights such as pledge and mortgage, crucial to a creditor\'s position.',
    'ri.law.4.t': 'EU Insolvency Regulation',
    'ri.law.4.d': 'Governs the recognition of insolvency proceedings within the European Union.',
    'ri.law.5.t': 'Civil Directors Disqualification Act',
    'ri.law.5.d': 'Allows a director to be temporarily barred from managing a legal entity following bankruptcy fraud.',
    'ri.div.label': 'Practice areas',
