    'csu.faq.label': 'FAQ',
    'csu.faq.title': 'Frequently asked questions',
    'csu.faq.0.q': 'What is sustainability consulting?',
    'csu.faq.0.a': 'It is the advisory field around making organisations more sustainable: consultants help set a sustainability strategy, reduce emissions, work circularly and meet rules such as the CSRD.',
    'csu.faq.1.q': 'What degree do I need?',
    'csu.faq.1.a': 'The routes are broad. Students come from business, economics, technical and sustainability programmes. Affinity with sustainability and analytical ability are important.',
    'csu.faq.2.q': 'What does a sustainability consultant do day to day?',
    'csu.faq.2.a': 'Consultants set strategy, measure emissions, build roadmaps, guide CSRD reporting and help organisations meet their sustainability goals.',
    'csu.faq.3.q': 'What is the CSRD?',
    'csu.faq.3.a': 'The CSRD is the European directive that requires large companies to report on their sustainability, which has strongly increased demand for sustainability consulting.',
    'csu.faq.4.q': 'Is sustainability consulting a growing field?',
    'csu.faq.4.a': 'Yes. Partly due to rules such as the CSRD and the attention to climate, sustainability is one of the fastest-growing parts of consulting.',
    'csu.faq.5.q': 'How much do you earn in sustainability consulting?',
    'csu.faq.5.a': 'Pay depends strongly on the type of employer and is typically higher at a strategy house than at a small specialist firm. Actual pay is listed where known in the vacancies on this site.',
    'csu.faq.6.q': 'What skills do you need?',
    'csu.faq.6.a': 'Analytical thinking, knowledge of sustainability, numeracy, communication and the ability to connect ambition and feasibility.',
    'csu.faq.7.q': 'How do I get into this field as a student?',
    'csu.faq.7.a': 'Get to know sustainability and the CSRD, do a relevant internship, and apply via campus or the firm\'s website.',
    'csu.rel.label': 'Related',
    'csu.rel.title': 'Related consulting paths',
    'csu.end.title': 'Start your journey in sustainability consulting',
    'csu.end.sub': 'Browse open vacancies or discover the other consulting paths.',
    'cpo.badge': 'Consulting career path',
    'cpo.h1': 'People & Organisation Consulting',
    'cpo.sub': 'Discover what people & organisation consulting involves: how consultants help organisations with change, structure, talent and culture, what they do day to day, the career ladder, and how students prepare for an application.',
    'cpo.cta.vac': 'View vacancies',
    'cpo.cta.paths': 'Explore consulting paths',
    'cpo.intro.label': 'Introduction',
    'cpo.intro.title': 'What is people & organisation consulting?',
    'cpo.intro.p': 'People & organisation consulting is about the human side of an organisation: how you design a company, carry out change, develop talent and build a culture in which people perform. Consultants help organisations translate their strategy into the right structure, roles and way of working.',
    'cpo.intro.p2': 'The work combines analysis with behaviour: a new structure or strategy only works once people actually work differently. The consultant therefore switches between design on paper and what it really takes to bring an organisation along.',
    'cpo.intro.p3': 'People & organisation is a broad and sought-after field, partly due to reorganisations, mergers and the tight labour market. It appeals to students who want to combine analytical work with the human side of organisations.',
    'cpo.w1.t': 'What it is',
    'cpo.w1.d': 'The advisory field around the people and organisation side of a company, from structure to culture.',
    'cpo.w2.t': 'What it centres on',
    'cpo.w2.d': 'Translating strategy into the right structure, roles, talent and way of working.',
    'cpo.w3.t': 'Why clients need it',
    'cpo.w3.d': 'To reorganise, merge, retain talent and truly carry out change.',
    'cpo.w4.t': 'Why students find it attractive',
    'cpo.w4.d': 'Combining analytical work with the human side of organisations.',
    'cpo.tier.label': 'The practice',
    'cpo.tier.title': 'Three settings where you practise this field',
    'cpo.tier.text': 'The breakdown below mainly says something about the type of employer and the clients you serve, not about the quality of the work.',
    'cpo.tier.0.t': 'Talent and reward firms',
    'cpo.tier.0.d': 'International firms focused on talent, leadership, reward and organisation design.',
    'cpo.tier.1.t': 'Organisation and change advisory firms',
    'cpo.tier.1.d': 'Firms that focus on organisational change, structure and the way of working.',
    'cpo.tier.2.t': 'Strategy houses and the Big Four',
    'cpo.tier.2.d': 'The large advisory and strategy houses with a people and change practice.',
    'cpo.tier.text2': 'Talent and reward firms are strong in leadership, reward and measuring organisations. Organisation and change advisory firms go deep into structure and change. The strategy houses and the Big Four link the people side to large strategic and digital projects. In addition, many specialists work in-house in an HR or transformation team.',
    'cpo.do.label': 'What they do',
    'cpo.do.title': 'What people & organisation consultants do',
    'cpo.do.text': 'The work differs by project, but the building blocks below come up in almost every people project.',
    'cpo.do.0.t': '(Re)designing organisations',
    'cpo.do.0.d': 'Redesigning structure, roles and responsibilities.',
    'cpo.do.1.t': 'Guiding change',
    'cpo.do.1.d': 'Bringing the organisation along so a new way of working sticks.',
    'cpo.do.2.t': 'Talent and succession',
    'cpo.do.2.d': 'Mapping talent, developing it and planning succession.',
    'cpo.do.3.t': 'Developing leadership',
    'cpo.do.3.d': 'Making leaders and teams stronger in their role.',
    'cpo.do.4.t': 'Reward and performance',
    'cpo.do.4.d': 'Designing reward structures and performance agreements.',
    'cpo.do.5.t': 'Culture and behaviour',
    'cpo.do.5.d': 'Working on culture, collaboration and desired behaviour.',
    'cpo.do.6.t': 'HR transformation',
    'cpo.do.6.d': 'Renewing the HR function and its processes and systems.',
    'cpo.do.7.t': 'People analytics',
    'cpo.do.7.d': 'Using data about employees to underpin choices.',
    'cpo.law.label': 'Types of project',
    'cpo.law.title': 'The main types of project',
    'cpo.law.text': 'People & organisation consulting has a number of recurring project types, even though the sector and the trigger differ greatly.',
    'cpo.law.0.t': 'Organisation design',
    'cpo.law.0.d': 'Redesigning the structure and roles of an organisation.',
